It seems to me that you are trying to deserialize a `Posiciones` array, but you are receiving an object which contains an array of `Posiciones`s. So you are expecting `[{&quot;chapa&quot;: &quot;abc&quot;, ...}, {&quot;chapa&quot;: &quot;efg&quot;, ...}, ...]` but receiving `{&quot;posiciones&quot;: [{&quot;chapa&quot;: &quot;abc&quot;, ...}, {&quot;chapa&quot;: &quot;efg&quot;, ...}, ...]}`. If it is the case, just wrap the array in an object:

    public class PosicionesResponse {

      private Posiciones[] posiciones;

      //constructors, getters, setters

    }

Then you can perform the request this way:

    ResponseEntity&lt;PosicionesResponse&gt; response = restTemplate.exchange(url, HttpMethod.GET, requestEntity, PosicionesResponse.class);

This is due to a security feature discussed in [logback#596](https://github.com/qos-ch/logback/discussions/596).

You need to remove `pull-parser` from your dependency list:
```lang-xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;dom4j&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;dom4j&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;1.5.2&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;exclusions&gt;
        &lt;exclusion&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;pull-parser&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;pull-parser&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;/exclusion&gt;
    &lt;/exclusions&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

Your application will fall back to using the Xerces fork included in every recent JRE, which supports the `http://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities` feature.

**Remark**: When you asked your question the Dom4j version you were using was 17 years old and had already 2 CVEs published, one of them concerned external entities.

